Durban - Police have opened an inquest docket into the death of a 15-year-old Pietermaritzburg teenager who was found with a gunshot wound to her stomach on Saturday afternoon.The city&#x2019;s police spokesman, Mthokozisi Ngobese, said on Sunday that a gun had been found at the scene.He refused to divulge who the gun belonged to.&#x201C;We do not suspect foul play,&#x201D; he said.The girl&#x2019;s family were battling to cope with their grief. Her father refused to give her name, talk about his daughter, or the incident.&#x201C;This just happened. We are emotional. Please respect that,&#x201D; he said.ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said that when paramedics arrived at the scene at 2.30pm, they were met by members of the family who escorted them to a nearby house. On arrival they found the 15-year-old lying in the garage of the home.&#x201C;Upon assessment they found that she showed no signs of life and appeared to have a gunshot wound to her stomach. Sadly, there was nothing that paramedics could do for her and she was declared dead on the scene. A firearm was found lying near the scene.&#x201D;He added that the paramedics handed the scene over to the local police.&#x201C;It is understood that her father found her in the garage and called emergency services,&#x201D; he said. Daily News IOL on Twitter IOL News on Facebook